description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in being part of a great team dedicated to providing chemotherapy to patients of East Kent?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;East Kent University NHS Foundation Trust (EKUFT) has an exciting and challenging new role within the pharmacy department and requires an enthusiastic, motivated individual to join our dynamic and lively department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be based in the Pharmacy Aseptic Unit at Kent and Canterbury and will supply medications to service users across the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will include managing stock, dispensing and manufacturing aseptically prepared medicines and ensuring Good Manufacturing Practice is upheld in supplying medicines to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No previous experience in Pharmacy is required as full in house training will be given. We are looking for applicants who are eager to learn, able to organise and prioritise their own work to meet deadlines, and able to work using their own initiative. Whilst applicants should ideally have an NVQ level 2 in pharmacy services, those without will be expected to enrol and will be supported to work towards this qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJenny ClementsJob titleAseptic Production Unit ManagerEmail addressjenny.clements@nhs.netTelephone number01227 864340Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Lightfoot, Pharmacy Aseptics and Cancer Services Lead Pharmacist&lt;/p&gt;
